<subSubSection pageId="6" pageNumber="23" type="chorology">
<paragraph pageId="6" pageNumber="23">Chorology.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="6" pageNumber="23">
<taxonomicName authorityName="Puthz" authorityYear="1981" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Stenus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Stenus medus" order="Coleoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="23" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="medus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="23">Stenus medus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, described from Armenia, Azerbaijan, and northern Iran (
<bibRefCitation author="Puthz, V" journalOrPublisher="Revue Suisse de Zoologie" pageId="19" pageNumber="36" pagination="693 - 706" publicationUrl="10.5962/bhl.part.82401" refId="B56" refString="Puthz, V, 1981. Neue westpalaearktische Stenus, vorwiegend aus dem Genfer Museum (Coleoptera: Staphylinidae). 183. Beitrag zur Kenntnis der Steninen. Revue Suisse de Zoologie 83: 693 - 706, DOI: 10.5962/bhl.part.82401" title="Neue westpalaearktische Stenus, vorwiegend aus dem Genfer Museum (Coleoptera: Staphylinidae). 183. Beitrag zur Kenntnis der Steninen." url="10.5962/bhl.part.82401" volume="83" year="1981">Puthz 1981</bibRefCitation>
: 702), is widely distributed in Transcaucasia, Turkey, and northern and northwestern Iran between 44°00'E (Orumieh) and 53°00'E (Shahmirzad) (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figures 7–12" captionStartId="F2" captionText="Figures 7 - 12. Distribution of Steninae in Iran. 7. Stenus circularis species group: ○ Stenus planifrons robustus; 8. Stenus clavicornis species group: ○ Stenus caspius, ● Stenus providus providus; 9. Stenus comma species group: ■ Stenus aereus, ○ Stenus asiaticus, ● Stenus bicornis, ▲ Stenus biguttatus, □ Stenus comma comma; 10. Stenus cordatus species group: ○ Stenus araxis, ● Stenus turk; 11. Stenus crassus and Stenus fornicatus species groups: ■ Stenus crassus, △ Stenus formicetorum, ○ Stenus fornicatus; 12. Stenus glacialis species group: ➕ Stenus armeniacus, ▲ Stenus hospes, ■ Stenus limicola, ○ Stenus medus, ▲ Stenus parcior, □ Stenus persicus, ● Stenus schah." figureDoi="10.3897/dez.63.5885.figures7-12" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/74429" pageId="6" pageNumber="23">12</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="6" pageNumber="23" type="biogeographical characterization">
<paragraph pageId="6" pageNumber="23">Biogeographical characterization.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="6" pageNumber="23">
Due to its distribution in Transcaucasia and its high abundance in the Hyrcanian zone in the northern slopes of the Elburz Mountains, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Puthz" authorityYear="1981" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Stenus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Stenus medus" order="Coleoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="23" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="medus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="23">Stenus medus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is a typical expansive Caspian faunal element.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
